# Ananke demo scene recipe
#
# This repository cannot author Unity scene YAML safely without Unity-generated
# .meta GUIDs, so the demo scene is expressed as a deterministic setup recipe
# for the scripts now committed in Assets/Ananke/Scripts.
#
# Scene contents
#  - Empty GameObject: "AnankeRuntime"
#  - Components on that GameObject:
#      * Ananke.AnankeReceiver
#      * Ananke.AnankeController
#  - No entity assignments required: AnankeController auto-creates two
#    placeholder rigs with mapped bones named Head, Torso, LeftArm, RightArm,
#    LeftLeg, RightLeg, and Pelvis.
#  - Optional floor: Unity Plane at (0, 0, 0)
#  - Optional Camera: position (0, 3, -8), rotation (18, 0, 0)
#  - Optional Directional Light: rotation (50, -30, 0)
#
# Runtime behaviour
#  - The receiver opens ws://127.0.0.1:3001/stream.
#  - The controller consumes snapshot frames and applies root translation plus
#    simple pose scaling/tilt to the placeholder rig bones.
#  - Body tint moves toward yellow as shockQ rises and turns grey on death.
#
# Editor steps
#  1. Open the Unity project.
#  2. Create a new empty scene.
#  3. Add the runtime GameObject and the two scripts above.
#  4. Save as Assets/Ananke/AnankeDemo.unity.
#  5. Start the sidecar with: cd sidecar && npm start
#  6. Press Play.
